{"word":"δαλός","slug":"δαλός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δαλός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:δαίω'><el>δαίω1</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a fire-brand, piece of blazing wood</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a thunderbolt</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a burnt-out torch</i>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of an old man, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}